ARE YOU THE FASTEST KID IN CHICAGO???? 

BOWA Gives, a local nonprofit that supports mentoring youth through sports is putting on a fantastic event for the youth ! 

The track competition will be open to boys and girls between the ages of 5 to 14 years old.
The fastest kids in Chicago will participate in timed, 60-meter, 200- meter and 400- meter races on Saturday, December 17 at the Dr. Conrad Worrill Track & Field Center at Gately Park, 10201 S. Cottage Grove Ave. The one-day timed sprints and mid- distance races will take place from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. 

The public is invited to attend for free to support Chicago’s local sprinters.
For more information and to register, visit 

www.chicagoparkdistrict.com/fastest-kids.

These words help me crawl out of the darkest of places ….. REMEMBER YOUR WORDS! #livingproof

🗣️ “From all these obstacles that I’ve had, I’ve never really seen it as an opportunity to quit this thing. A lot of people tell me, ‘You’ve been through so much. Why don’t you just hang it up? You’ve gone to the Olympics. You’ve brought home two medals. You’ve been top 10 all-time in your sport. You’ve done enough.’ I’m addicted to it. Until that burning desire goes away, I’m gonna continue to run and be the fighter that I am.”

@ughlyducklin is a two-time Olympian and has two Olympic medals from the 4x100m relay including gold from the Summer Games in Rio in 2016. She has two World Championship silver medals in the relay as well. She is a two-time U.S. champion and her personal best of 10.74 puts her at No. 10 on the all-time world list and No. 5 on the all-time U.S. list for the event.

The New Jersey native really popped off nationally as a star at @oregontf, where she won five NCAA titles.

Over the past decade, she has defied the odds and fought to remain atop the sport. The journey has included injuries, COVID, depression, anxiety, homelessness as a high schooler, family cancer battles and much more. 

I’ve been a fan of English for years because of the beast she unleashes on the track and I’m so glad we finally got to sit down and chat for the podcast.

🎧 Stream, download and listen to The CITIUS MAG Podcast wherever you get your shows.

🚨 Please be aware that this conversation contains sensitive mental health content. If you are struggling or need support, @988lifeline is available 24/7/365 for free, confidential crisis counseling. Dial 988 or text TALK to 741741
